            <title>[CASSANDRA-6856] StorageProxy registers new instance with JMX not this instance</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6856</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The StorageProxy uses the lovely singleton pattern. However JMX registers a new instance of StorageProxy class not the singleton. I am not sure the bug is outward facing but it someone were to add a class level variable inside the storage proxy and manipulate it through JMX then it would be exposed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
